INSERTION

This is the first big operation.

Suppose:

[2,4,5,10,8]

Insert:

1

Step 1:

Put at end.

[2,4,5,10,8,1]

Tree:

        2
      /   \
     4     5
    / \   /
   10 8  1

Violation:

1 < 5

Swap.

[2,4,1,10,8,5]

Again:

1 < 2

Swap.

[1,4,2,10,8,5]

Done.

This process:

Bubble Up
Heapify Up
Percolate Up

All same thing.DELETION

Heap deletes ONLY ROOT.

Because root is minimum.

Current:

[1,4,2,10,8,5]

Delete minimum.

Step 1

Move last element to root.

[5,4,2,10,8]

Now broken.

        5
      /   \
     4     2

Step 2

Swap with smaller child.

2

Result:

[2,4,5,10,8]

Done.

This process:

Heapify Down
Bubble Down
Sink Down

